    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-11-01T01:24:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-11-01T01:24:00-05:00" n="251"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d251">
                <head>251. Telegram From the Commander, Military Assistance Command, Vietnam
                        (<persName corresp="#p_HGPD1" type="from">Harkins</persName>) to the
                    Director of the National Security Agency (<persName corresp="#p_BLGGA1"
                        type="to">Blake</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d251fn1"
                        >Source: Department of State, Central Files, <gloss target="#t_POL1"
                            >POL</gloss> 26 <gloss target="#t_S1">S</gloss> VIET. Secret; Flash. The
                        source text is the copy sent for information Flash to the Department of
                        State. Also sent for information Flash to <gloss target="#t_USIB1"
                            >USIB</gloss> agencies. Received at the Department of State at 1:44
                        a.m.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Saigon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1963-11-01T14:24:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1963—2:24 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_DTG1">DTG</gloss> 010624Z November. Critic. At 1345H General
                        <persName corresp="#p_DON1">Don</persName> telephoned <persName
                        corresp="#p_SMGRG1">Stilwell</persName>, J-3 and stated in the clear all
                        (<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>)<note n="2" xml:id="d251fn2">As on the source
                        text.</note> Generals were assembled with him at <gloss target="#t_JGS1"
                        >JGS</gloss> HQ and were initiating a coup. <persName corresp="#p_SMGRG1"
                        >Stilwell</persName> asked if timing was immediate and was told yes.
                        <persName corresp="#p_DON1">Don</persName> asked that I be informed at
                    once.</p>
                <p>I notified Ambassador at 1400. He had just received info that Marine unit had
                    seized the <gloss target="#t_PTT1">PTT</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_CAS1"
                        >CAS</gloss> reports unidentified elms have seized central Police
                    station.</p>
                <p>Army elms (presumably 3rd Airborne Bn) are on road from airfield to Saigon.
                    Reports of fighting at Special Forces HQ adjacent to <gloss target="#t_JGS1"
                        >JGS</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Ambassador and I have directed <gloss target="#t_AFRS1">AFRS</gloss> to broadcast
                    warning to US personnel to stay off streets in view reported civil
                    disturbances.</p>
                <p>Numerous troop movements reported this morning. All details later. Will keep you
                    advised.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
